headline: Weather Advisory for Ireland
description:
Sunday, Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday will be very cold with temperatures in low single figures by day and with sharp or severe frosts and icy patches at night. 

Showers of sleet or snow at times in eastern counties from Sunday evening onwards.

Hazardous conditions on roads and paths.

headline: Wind warning for Galway, Mayo, Kerry
description:
Southerly winds, veering southwesterly, will reach mean speeds of 50 to 65km/h with gusts of up to 100km/h, higher in coastal areas and on high ground.

Localised wave overtopping is possible.

headline: Wind warning for Donegal
description: West to northwest winds will widely reach mean speeds of 50 to 60km/h with gusts of 90 to 100km/h. Winds will be stronger near coastal areas, where localised wave overtopping is possible, and on high ground.
